article.headline: Rider 75, Manhattan 56
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. (AP) -- Edwin Muniz scored 27 points to lead Rider to a 75-56 victory over cold-shooting Manhattan Tuesday night. The loss knocked Manhattan (11-6, 7-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) out of first place. Rider (6-11, 2-7 MAAC) jumped out to an early 18-5 lead and increased the margin to 17 by halftime. Rider led 47-28 before Manhattan (11-6, 7-2 MAAC) went on an 18-8 run to cut the lead to 55-46 with 7:44 left to play. That was as close as the Jaspers got. Terrance Mouton had 19 points for Rider, and Jason Thompson had his sixth double-double of the season, with 13 points and a career-high 15 rebounds. Arturo DuBois led Manhattan with 16 points and 11 rebounds, and Jeff Xavier added 14. The Jaspers shot just 32 percent from the field, while Rider shot 47 percent. Manhattan's leading scorer, CJ Anderson, was suspended indefinitely for academic reasons and did not dress for the game.
